# Global Rules

- TypeScript **strict** mode everywhere; `noImplicitAny`, `strictNullChecks` on
- Clean Architecture + SOLID + DRY + KISS
- Repository Pattern; Dependency Injection for all services
- Never use `any`; prefer `unknown` + narrow, or explicit types
- No duplicated logic — extract shared modules under `libs/` or shared packages
- Prefer small, single-purpose modules/files
- Log every meaningful action (start, success, failure) with structured context
- All configuration via environment variables; never hardcode secrets or URLs
- Do not mix layers: orchestration ≠ business logic ≠ browser automation ≠ LLM text
- Prefer idempotent, restartable operations
